task.summary: -- Initial attempt at solving beverage with condiment problem before reading chapter.
-- Solution to solving the condiment problem by making condiments act as decorators for beverages.
-- Finished last touch changes on factory method example -- Added Design Patterns NOTES file

-- Made a couple of changes to show how we are placing too much responsibility for pizza creation in the PizzaShops themselves, giving them the ability to create their own types of Pizza. This preps us for the discussion of introducing a factory for the pizzas to avoid rogue shops.

-- Command - implemented a remote control that we can assign commands to. The commands are invoked by the invoker (the RC). Each command has a reference to it's receiver and operates directly on it. Receiver has no knowledge of command, nor does the invoker.
-- Command - added simple "undo method" implementations to the less complex commands.

-- Command - added more complex "undo method" implementation that tracks multiple states for a single device. The fan now remembers if it was on medium before, for example, and will go back to that if undo is pressed.

-- Command - added a macro command that implements the command interface, but under the hood fires multiple commands. Undo functionality is easily achieved because the individual commands worry about themselves independently.

MESSAGE.value: -- Introduced strategy pattern for fly behavior. Also demonstrate runtime behavior change.
-- Strategy pattern - organized packages and added a couple of small comments
-- Observer pattern - first test to ensure when we register an observer, it is indeed there and observing.
-- Observer pattern - setting new weather data on the coordinator now updates the vals on all of the observers. Test in place to support.

-- Observer pattern - added a Demo class and a couple of Device (observer) implementations to demonstrate usage. Much refactoring. Final checkin before conversion to using the built-in java.util Observer/Observable apis.
-- Observer pattern - conversion to use the built-in java.util Observer/Observable apis.
